00:01:08.650 --> 00:01:10.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Thanks for all coming.

00:01:10.410 --> 00:01:12.560 align:middle line:84%
This is our biggest
seminar ever.

00:01:12.560 --> 00:01:15.650 align:middle line:84%
I started doing this about
three years ago in my house

00:01:15.650 --> 00:01:19.250 align:middle line:84%
with 20 people doing
a one-day seminar.

00:01:19.250 --> 00:01:22.970 align:middle line:84%
And then about two years ago, we
started taking it on the road,

00:01:22.970 --> 00:01:26.390 align:middle line:84%
and we did a seminar for
about 100 people in Brisbane

00:01:26.390 --> 00:01:28.340 align:middle line:90%
in a church.

00:01:28.340 --> 00:01:30.000 align:middle line:84%
And I was pretty
amazed with that.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:35.300 align:middle line:84%
And now, we've got a room
with 450 people in it.

00:01:35.300 --> 00:01:37.490 align:middle line:90%
It's pretty amazing.

00:01:37.490 --> 00:01:41.840 align:middle line:84%
And the message that I have
is a very different message

00:01:41.840 --> 00:01:45.710 align:middle line:84%
to anything I've ever seen
that's out there in terms

00:01:45.710 --> 00:01:47.330 align:middle line:90%
of weight loss.

00:01:47.330 --> 00:01:51.400 align:middle line:84%
Every diet program approach
I've ever seen in weight loss

00:01:51.400 --> 00:01:54.320 align:middle line:84%
all functions on a basic
paradigm that you can somehow

00:01:54.320 --> 00:01:59.000 align:middle line:84%
force yourself to lose weight,
either through willpower,

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:03.320 align:middle line:84%
just gutting it out,
some sort of program

00:02:03.320 --> 00:02:07.400 align:middle line:84%
with a eat whatever you want
once a day, or once a week,

00:02:07.400 --> 00:02:09.410 align:middle line:84%
or whatever it is-- it's
just always a program.

00:02:09.410 --> 00:02:12.560 align:middle line:84%
But the idea is, you can manage
yourself, maintain yourself

00:02:12.560 --> 00:02:14.450 align:middle line:84%
through behavior
modification, somehow force

00:02:14.450 --> 00:02:18.300 align:middle line:84%
yourself to lose weight and
keep it off in the long term.

00:02:18.300 --> 00:02:21.230 align:middle line:84%
And that's not
been my experience.

00:02:21.230 --> 00:02:23.270 align:middle line:84%
My experience is that
when your body wants

00:02:23.270 --> 00:02:25.010 align:middle line:84%
to be fat for
whatever reason, it's

00:02:25.010 --> 00:02:27.420 align:middle line:84%
going to force you
to gain weight.

00:02:27.420 --> 00:02:31.320 align:middle line:84%
And if you try to fight it,
it's going to fight back.

00:02:31.320 --> 00:02:35.340 align:middle line:84%
And you can control what
you eat in the short term.

00:02:35.340 --> 00:02:37.862 align:middle line:84%
But you can't control
how hungry you are.

00:02:37.862 --> 00:02:38.662 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:02:38.662 --> 00:02:41.590 align:middle line:90%


00:02:41.590 --> 00:02:44.500 align:middle line:84%
And you can't control the
types of foods you're craving.

00:02:44.500 --> 00:02:46.720 align:middle line:84%
And if your body
wants to be fat,

00:02:46.720 --> 00:02:49.833 align:middle line:84%
it will make you insatiably
hungry for the most

00:02:49.833 --> 00:02:50.875 align:middle line:90%
fattening foods possible.

00:02:50.875 --> 00:02:53.500 align:middle line:90%


00:02:53.500 --> 00:02:56.180 align:middle line:84%
But my approach
is very different.

00:02:56.180 --> 00:03:01.200 align:middle line:84%
My approach functions on a
very different basic paradigm.

00:03:01.200 --> 00:03:07.110 align:middle line:84%
And that is that if you can get
your body to want to be thin,

00:03:07.110 --> 00:03:08.673 align:middle line:84%
then it all happens
automatically.

00:03:08.673 --> 00:03:10.090 align:middle line:84%
There's no more
managing yourself.

00:03:10.090 --> 00:03:11.890 align:middle line:84%
There's no more
maintenance schedule.

00:03:11.890 --> 00:03:13.440 align:middle line:84%
There's no more
counting calories.

00:03:13.440 --> 00:03:16.220 align:middle line:84%
There's no more good
days and bad days.

00:03:16.220 --> 00:03:18.480 align:middle line:90%
You simply crave less food.

00:03:18.480 --> 00:03:19.980 align:middle line:90%
You crave healthier food.

00:03:19.980 --> 00:03:23.110 align:middle line:84%
Your metabolism
actually speeds up,

00:03:23.110 --> 00:03:25.180 align:middle line:84%
and you become more
efficient at burning fat.

00:03:25.180 --> 00:03:26.900 align:middle line:84%
And so it all happens
automatically.

00:03:26.900 --> 00:03:30.040 align:middle line:84%
And then once the
weight's off, there's

00:03:30.040 --> 00:03:34.312 align:middle line:84%
no more maintenance schedule
that you have to worry about.

00:03:34.312 --> 00:03:36.520 align:middle line:84%
And there's no worrying
about keeping it off forever,

00:03:36.520 --> 00:03:38.478 align:middle line:84%
because you weren't
dieting in the first place.

00:03:38.478 --> 00:03:40.940 align:middle line:90%


00:03:40.940 --> 00:03:43.730 align:middle line:84%
You simply worked with
your body and your body's

00:03:43.730 --> 00:03:46.280 align:middle line:84%
basic principles to get
it to want to be thin.

00:03:46.280 --> 00:03:50.747 align:middle line:90%


00:03:50.747 --> 00:03:52.830 align:middle line:84%
And the message has spread
all over the world now.

00:03:52.830 --> 00:03:55.450 align:middle line:90%


00:03:55.450 --> 00:03:58.960 align:middle line:84%
As Jack said, the book's being
translated into 15 languages.

00:03:58.960 --> 00:04:01.750 align:middle line:84%
And next week, we launch our
Spanish website, El Metado

00:04:01.750 --> 00:04:04.520 align:middle line:90%
Gabriel.

00:04:04.520 --> 00:04:09.450 align:middle line:84%
And there's a million others
that I can't even pronounce

00:04:09.450 --> 00:04:11.790 align:middle line:90%
in different languages.

00:04:11.790 --> 00:04:14.040 align:middle line:84%
But we're going to take
it all over the world now.

00:04:14.040 --> 00:04:15.600 align:middle line:84%
And the reason
why it's spreading

00:04:15.600 --> 00:04:17.519 align:middle line:84%
is because people know
that diets don't work.

00:04:17.519 --> 00:04:19.180 align:middle line:90%
People have tried it.

00:04:19.180 --> 00:04:19.980 align:middle line:90%
And let's face it.

00:04:19.980 --> 00:04:24.330 align:middle line:84%
If diets worked,
there'd be one diet.

00:04:24.330 --> 00:04:27.715 align:middle line:84%
Everybody would lose weight,
and that would be the end of it.

00:04:27.715 --> 00:04:29.340 align:middle line:84%
There wouldn't be
1,000 diets out there

00:04:29.340 --> 00:04:33.390 align:middle line:84%
and a new diet every week, the
avocado diet, the soup diet,

00:04:33.390 --> 00:04:37.350 align:middle line:84%
the chicken diet, the doctor
this diet, the once a week

00:04:37.350 --> 00:04:42.730 align:middle line:84%
diet-- whatever it is,
there'd be one diet.

00:04:42.730 --> 00:04:45.420 align:middle line:84%
Everybody would lose weight,
and that would be the end of it.

00:04:45.420 --> 00:04:48.190 align:middle line:90%


00:04:48.190 --> 00:04:49.750 align:middle line:90%
Diets don't work.

00:04:49.750 --> 00:04:52.570 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going explain to you
exactly why diets don't work--

00:04:52.570 --> 00:04:55.090 align:middle line:84%
chemically, physically,
theoretically,

00:04:55.090 --> 00:04:57.700 align:middle line:90%
exactly why diets don't work.

00:04:57.700 --> 00:05:00.490 align:middle line:84%
And why every time
you go on a diet,

00:05:00.490 --> 00:05:02.775 align:middle line:84%
you lose weight
in the short term

00:05:02.775 --> 00:05:04.150 align:middle line:84%
and then you have
these cravings,

00:05:04.150 --> 00:05:05.440 align:middle line:90%
and then you have this yo-yo.

00:05:05.440 --> 00:05:07.990 align:middle line:84%
And so people that have been
yo-yo dieting for 30 years

00:05:07.990 --> 00:05:12.413 align:middle line:84%
are now contacting, me
thousands of people,

00:05:12.413 --> 00:05:14.330 align:middle line:84%
and saying that they're
finally losing weight,

00:05:14.330 --> 00:05:16.027 align:middle line:90%
and they're not dieting.

00:05:16.027 --> 00:05:18.110 align:middle line:84%
And that's because they're
working with their body

00:05:18.110 --> 00:05:19.110 align:middle line:90%
rather than fighting it.

00:05:19.110 --> 00:05:22.290 align:middle line:90%


00:05:22.290 --> 00:05:24.540 align:middle line:84%
I always say that dieting
is a little bit like holding

00:05:24.540 --> 00:05:28.760 align:middle line:84%
a volleyball under water,
because the second you let go,

00:05:28.760 --> 00:05:32.302 align:middle line:90%
poof, it pops right up.

00:05:32.302 --> 00:05:33.260 align:middle line:90%
This is very different.

00:05:33.260 --> 00:05:34.760 align:middle line:84%
And it's based on
my own experience.

00:05:34.760 --> 00:05:38.300 align:middle line:84%
And I'll just tell you
a little bit about that.

00:05:38.300 --> 00:05:40.100 align:middle line:84%
Back in 1990, I
moved to New York,

00:05:40.100 --> 00:05:42.230 align:middle line:84%
and I started working
on Wall Street.

00:05:42.230 --> 00:05:46.730 align:middle line:84%
And back then, I was pretty
much exactly the way I am now.

00:05:46.730 --> 00:05:50.047 align:middle line:84%
And I was pretty much one of
those naturally thin people.

00:05:50.047 --> 00:05:51.880 align:middle line:84%
You know the types we
all hate that can just

00:05:51.880 --> 00:05:55.690 align:middle line:84%
eat whatever they want and just
never have to think about it?

00:05:55.690 --> 00:05:57.130 align:middle line:90%
I was like that.

00:05:57.130 --> 00:05:59.377 align:middle line:84%
I didn't have to
think about weight.

00:05:59.377 --> 00:06:00.960 align:middle line:84%
And I moved to New
York, and I started

00:06:00.960 --> 00:06:03.820 align:middle line:84%
working in a high stress
job on Wall Street.

00:06:03.820 --> 00:06:09.290 align:middle line:84%
I was making $300 a week as
a bond trading assistant.

00:06:09.290 --> 00:06:12.530 align:middle line:90%
And my rent was $400 a week.

00:06:12.530 --> 00:06:14.930 align:middle line:90%
It was a pretty stressful job.

00:06:14.930 --> 00:06:18.710 align:middle line:84%
And as soon as I moved to New
York, I started gaining weight.

00:06:18.710 --> 00:06:20.960 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't think too much
about it in the beginning.

00:06:20.960 --> 00:06:23.120 align:middle line:84%
I gained maybe five
kilos, or 10 pounds

00:06:23.120 --> 00:06:26.300 align:middle line:84%
in the beginning in the first
year and maybe another five

00:06:26.300 --> 00:06:29.390 align:middle line:84%
kilos, or 10 pounds
in the second year.

00:06:29.390 --> 00:06:31.460 align:middle line:84%
And everybody gains weight
when they start a job.

00:06:31.460 --> 00:06:32.840 align:middle line:84%
You know, you're
sitting in an office,

00:06:32.840 --> 00:06:34.507 align:middle line:84%
you're working at a
computer, you're not

00:06:34.507 --> 00:06:36.020 align:middle line:84%
thinking about
what you're eating,

00:06:36.020 --> 00:06:37.562 align:middle line:84%
and I didn't think
too much about it.

00:06:37.562 --> 00:06:40.460 align:middle line:84%
But after a couple of
years, I just kept gaining.

00:06:40.460 --> 00:06:41.630 align:middle line:90%
And it didn't stop.

00:06:41.630 --> 00:06:43.520 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, after
a couple of years,

00:06:43.520 --> 00:06:47.090 align:middle line:84%
I was about 100
kilos, or 220 pounds.

00:06:47.090 --> 00:06:48.920 align:middle line:84%
And I decided that
I was going to try

00:06:48.920 --> 00:06:53.180 align:middle line:84%
to do something about it, and
I did what everybody does.

00:06:53.180 --> 00:06:54.182 align:middle line:90%
I went on a diet.

00:06:54.182 --> 00:06:55.640 align:middle line:84%
Because it just
makes sense, right?

00:06:55.640 --> 00:06:56.240 align:middle line:90%
Calories in.

00:06:56.240 --> 00:06:57.040 align:middle line:90%
Calories out.

00:06:57.040 --> 00:06:58.460 align:middle line:90%
Just cut the calories.

00:06:58.460 --> 00:07:01.850 align:middle line:90%
So I went on a diet.

00:07:01.850 --> 00:07:05.070 align:middle line:84%
And actually, I went
on a lot of diets.

00:07:05.070 --> 00:07:08.340 align:middle line:84%
And every diet or program I went
on all had the same pattern.

00:07:08.340 --> 00:07:10.590 align:middle line:84%
There'd be a whole list of
things I can't have, right?

00:07:10.590 --> 00:07:13.850 align:middle line:84%
No wheat, no fat,
no sugar, no salt.

00:07:13.850 --> 00:07:16.400 align:middle line:84%
Whatever it was, I'd follow
the diet to the letter,

00:07:16.400 --> 00:07:19.340 align:middle line:84%
because I am a fairly
disciplined person.

00:07:19.340 --> 00:07:20.900 align:middle line:84%
I'd follow the
diet to the letter.

00:07:20.900 --> 00:07:23.840 align:middle line:84%
I'd lose weight, which
you can do, right?

00:07:23.840 --> 00:07:25.310 align:middle line:90%
You can lose weight on a diet.

00:07:25.310 --> 00:07:26.470 align:middle line:90%
And I did lose weight.

00:07:26.470 --> 00:07:29.470 align:middle line:84%
I'd lose maybe 10
pounds, or five kilos.

00:07:29.470 --> 00:07:32.970 align:middle line:84%
And what would happen is, after
about two weeks or three weeks

00:07:32.970 --> 00:07:34.970 align:middle line:84%
of hard work, and I'm
feeling good about myself,

00:07:34.970 --> 00:07:37.310 align:middle line:90%
and I've lost the weight--

00:07:37.310 --> 00:07:41.910 align:middle line:84%
I'm still on the diet, and
I'm not losing weight anymore.

00:07:41.910 --> 00:07:45.970 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know if you've
ever had this experience, where

00:07:45.970 --> 00:07:49.410 align:middle line:84%
you're dieting and you're just
not losing weight anymore.

00:07:49.410 --> 00:07:53.460 align:middle line:84%
And I'm fighting
cravings left and right.

00:07:53.460 --> 00:07:55.920 align:middle line:84%
And the smell of
pizza in New York

00:07:55.920 --> 00:07:58.980 align:middle line:84%
is at every single
street corner.

00:07:58.980 --> 00:08:00.880 align:middle line:84%
And nobody makes pizza
like New Yorkers.

00:08:00.880 --> 00:08:01.680 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

00:08:01.680 --> 00:08:03.840 align:middle line:84%
It's the best pizza
in the universe.

00:08:03.840 --> 00:08:05.340 align:middle line:90%
It's this thin crust.

00:08:05.340 --> 00:08:07.000 align:middle line:90%
It's a big piece.

00:08:07.000 --> 00:08:08.580 align:middle line:90%
They're like $1.50 a slice.

00:08:08.580 --> 00:08:11.910 align:middle line:84%
They sit out on the
lights waiting for you.

00:08:11.910 --> 00:08:13.768 align:middle line:84%
And there's smell at
every single corner.

00:08:13.768 --> 00:08:15.685 align:middle line:84%
And there's this kind
of science to it, right?

00:08:15.685 --> 00:08:17.340 align:middle line:84%
You don't want to get the pizza
when it's right out the oven,

00:08:17.340 --> 00:08:18.722 align:middle line:90%
because the crust is too soft.

00:08:18.722 --> 00:08:21.180 align:middle line:84%
You want it to sit under the
lights for about an hour, hour

00:08:21.180 --> 00:08:22.060 align:middle line:90%
and a half.

00:08:22.060 --> 00:08:23.060 align:middle line:90%
And it gets real crispy.

00:08:23.060 --> 00:08:24.805 align:middle line:84%
If it sits too long,
it gets too crumbly.

00:08:24.805 --> 00:08:25.680 align:middle line:90%
And you just know it.

00:08:25.680 --> 00:08:27.420 align:middle line:84%
Like as soon as you a
pizza, you know exactly--

00:08:27.420 --> 00:08:27.970 align:middle line:90%
that's 20 minutes.

00:08:27.970 --> 00:08:28.770 align:middle line:90%
That's perfect.

00:08:28.770 --> 00:08:29.890 align:middle line:90%
I'll take that.

00:08:29.890 --> 00:08:30.690 align:middle line:90%
Not that slice.

00:08:30.690 --> 00:08:31.930 align:middle line:90%
No, that slice.

00:08:31.930 --> 00:08:33.263 align:middle line:90%
That's an hour and a half slice.

00:08:33.263 --> 00:08:34.539 align:middle line:90%
I don't want that.

00:08:34.539 --> 00:08:37.409 align:middle line:84%
So the smell of pizza would be
at every single street corner.

00:08:37.409 --> 00:08:39.582 align:middle line:84%
And then, I just
couldn't take it anymore.

00:08:39.582 --> 00:08:40.624 align:middle line:90%
And I had this big binge.

00:08:40.624 --> 00:08:44.110 align:middle line:90%


00:08:44.110 --> 00:08:47.530 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know if you've
ever had these big binges,

00:08:47.530 --> 00:08:49.690 align:middle line:84%
but I used to have
these big binges.

00:08:49.690 --> 00:08:52.060 align:middle line:84%
And then, like all the
weight, whatever I lost,

00:08:52.060 --> 00:08:54.760 align:middle line:84%
five kilos, 10 kilos, whatever
it was, it would come back,

00:08:54.760 --> 00:08:57.402 align:middle line:90%
poof, like that in two days.

00:08:57.402 --> 00:08:59.735 align:middle line:84%
And then two days later, I'd
be heavier than when I even

00:08:59.735 --> 00:09:00.535 align:middle line:90%
started the diet.

00:09:00.535 --> 00:09:04.500 align:middle line:90%


00:09:04.500 --> 00:09:06.700 align:middle line:90%
And I remember those binges.

00:09:06.700 --> 00:09:08.010 align:middle line:90%
I remember I once had--

00:09:08.010 --> 00:09:09.820 align:middle line:84%
when I was having one
of those bad days,

00:09:09.820 --> 00:09:11.653 align:middle line:84%
those binges where I
couldn't take anymore--

00:09:11.653 --> 00:09:14.680 align:middle line:84%
I once had three
delivery people show up

00:09:14.680 --> 00:09:19.940 align:middle line:84%
at my door at the same time,
all waiting for me to pay.

00:09:19.940 --> 00:09:21.350 align:middle line:84%
So here, I'm this
big guy, right?

00:09:21.350 --> 00:09:22.150 align:middle line:90%
I open the door.

00:09:22.150 --> 00:09:24.800 align:middle line:84%
There's three-- there's a
pizza guy, there's Chinese,

00:09:24.800 --> 00:09:26.300 align:middle line:84%
and McDonald's
delivers in New York.

00:09:26.300 --> 00:09:28.190 align:middle line:84%
You can get anything
you want in New York.

00:09:28.190 --> 00:09:30.023 align:middle line:84%
So there's three guys
waiting for me to pay.

00:09:30.023 --> 00:09:32.800 align:middle line:84%
So I try to make it off like
there's a party going on.

00:09:32.800 --> 00:09:35.240 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:09:35.240 --> 00:09:36.040 align:middle line:90%
Like, hold on guys.

00:09:36.040 --> 00:09:36.980 align:middle line:90%
I'll be right there.

00:09:36.980 --> 00:09:37.780 align:middle line:90%
How much is this?

00:09:37.780 --> 00:09:38.580 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:09:38.580 --> 00:09:42.980 align:middle line:90%


00:09:42.980 --> 00:09:46.120 align:middle line:84%
But I'd have this big binge,
and then, poof, all this weight

00:09:46.120 --> 00:09:49.090 align:middle line:90%
would come back, just like that.

00:09:49.090 --> 00:09:49.890 align:middle line:90%
Whatever it was.

00:09:49.890 --> 00:09:51.300 align:middle line:90%
Five kilos, 10 kilos, boom.

00:09:51.300 --> 00:09:52.330 align:middle line:90%
Right back.

00:09:52.330 --> 00:09:54.120 align:middle line:84%
And then two days
later, three days later,

00:09:54.120 --> 00:09:56.578 align:middle line:84%
I'm five kilos heavier than
when I'd even started the diet.

00:09:56.578 --> 00:09:58.380 align:middle line:84%
And this went on and
on and on and on.

00:09:58.380 --> 00:10:01.110 align:middle line:90%
Lose 10 kilos, gain 10.

00:10:01.110 --> 00:10:03.440 align:middle line:90%
Lose 10 kilos, gain 15.

00:10:03.440 --> 00:10:06.090 align:middle line:84%
It would go on and on and
on and on for like 11 years.

00:10:06.090 --> 00:10:08.900 align:middle line:90%


00:10:08.900 --> 00:10:10.660 align:middle line:84%
And when I say I
tried everything,

00:10:10.660 --> 00:10:13.180 align:middle line:84%
I mean I really,
really worked hard.

00:10:13.180 --> 00:10:16.310 align:middle line:84%
I used to work face to
face with Dr. Atkins.

00:10:16.310 --> 00:10:19.710 align:middle line:84%
You know Dr. Atkins
from the Atkins diet?

00:10:19.710 --> 00:10:21.030 align:middle line:90%
The no carb diet?

00:10:21.030 --> 00:10:22.830 align:middle line:84%
Who can go forever
without carbs, you know?

00:10:22.830 --> 00:10:24.620 align:middle line:90%
It's impossible.

00:10:24.620 --> 00:10:28.080 align:middle line:84%
But I worked face to face
with him for a month.

00:10:28.080 --> 00:10:31.208 align:middle line:90%
I spent over $3,000 with him.

00:10:31.208 --> 00:10:33.250 align:middle line:84%
And every Monday morning,
I'd go into his office.

00:10:33.250 --> 00:10:36.170 align:middle line:90%


00:10:36.170 --> 00:10:38.340 align:middle line:90%
And he was an angry old man.

00:10:38.340 --> 00:10:39.140 align:middle line:90%
I got to say.

00:10:39.140 --> 00:10:40.250 align:middle line:90%
I did not like Dr. Atkins.

00:10:40.250 --> 00:10:41.050 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

00:10:41.050 --> 00:10:42.508 align:middle line:84%
I'm going on the
record and saying,

00:10:42.508 --> 00:10:43.910 align:middle line:90%
I did not like Dr. Atkins.

00:10:43.910 --> 00:10:46.580 align:middle line:84%
I'm sitting in his
office, and he's

00:10:46.580 --> 00:10:49.280 align:middle line:84%
got this big, mahogany desk
and this big grandfather clock

00:10:49.280 --> 00:10:50.762 align:middle line:90%
that's going tick, tick, tick.

00:10:50.762 --> 00:10:52.970 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sitting there kind
of looking down like this,

00:10:52.970 --> 00:10:54.428 align:middle line:84%
and he's looking
at my test scores.

00:10:54.428 --> 00:10:56.990 align:middle line:84%
And I'm borderline type two
diabetic and metabolic syndrome

00:10:56.990 --> 00:10:59.570 align:middle line:84%
and triglycerides through the
roof and high blood pressure,

00:10:59.570 --> 00:11:02.010 align:middle line:84%
and blah, blah,
blah, blah, blah.

00:11:02.010 --> 00:11:03.100 align:middle line:90%
He just looks up at me.

00:11:03.100 --> 00:11:05.228 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sort of
looking down like that,

00:11:05.228 --> 00:11:06.645 align:middle line:84%
because I haven't
lost any weight.

00:11:06.645 --> 00:11:10.230 align:middle line:84%
He just looks up me and
goes, what are you doing?

00:11:10.230 --> 00:11:11.230 align:middle line:90%
You're killing yourself.

00:11:11.230 --> 00:11:16.440 align:middle line:90%


00:11:16.440 --> 00:11:20.885 align:middle line:84%
And I think to myself, is that
really the best you can do?

00:11:20.885 --> 00:11:22.510 align:middle line:84%
You know, you're Dr.
Atkins, and you've

00:11:22.510 --> 00:11:24.350 align:middle line:84%
sold 200 million
copies of your book.

00:11:24.350 --> 00:11:26.935 align:middle line:84%
And the best you can do is
yell at me for being so fat?

00:11:26.935 --> 00:11:30.520 align:middle line:84%
Like, I'm going to lose weight
because you're mad at me?

00:11:30.520 --> 00:11:33.900 align:middle line:90%
I don't have enough motivation?

00:11:33.900 --> 00:11:35.850 align:middle line:84%
You know, I've got
fitness trainers 7:00

00:11:35.850 --> 00:11:39.430 align:middle line:84%
in the morning I'm
meeting with, and I'm

00:11:39.430 --> 00:11:40.645 align:middle line:90%
going all day without carbs.

00:11:40.645 --> 00:11:43.650 align:middle line:90%


00:11:43.650 --> 00:11:45.400 align:middle line:84%
And then, I went to
the Pritikin Institute

00:11:45.400 --> 00:11:46.720 align:middle line:90%
in Santa Monica, California.

00:11:46.720 --> 00:11:47.950 align:middle line:90%
You know, the Pritikin diet?

00:11:47.950 --> 00:11:51.620 align:middle line:90%


00:11:51.620 --> 00:11:56.538 align:middle line:84%
Spent two weeks there and I
don't know, maybe $10,000.

00:11:56.538 --> 00:11:58.080 align:middle line:84%
And that's the exact
opposite, right?

00:11:58.080 --> 00:12:00.120 align:middle line:90%
That's the zero fat diet.

00:12:00.120 --> 00:12:02.218 align:middle line:90%
That's the all carb diet.

00:12:02.218 --> 00:12:03.018 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:12:03.018 --> 00:12:05.110 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:12:05.110 --> 00:12:07.980 align:middle line:84%
And so one week I'm
on the Atkins diet,

00:12:07.980 --> 00:12:10.590 align:middle line:84%
and I go into McDonald's and
I order a quarter pounder.

00:12:10.590 --> 00:12:12.060 align:middle line:90%
And I take the bread off.

00:12:12.060 --> 00:12:14.260 align:middle line:90%
I just eat the burger.

00:12:14.260 --> 00:12:17.460 align:middle line:84%
And the next week, I'm
on the Pritikin diet.

00:12:17.460 --> 00:12:19.380 align:middle line:84%
I go to the same
McDonald's, order

00:12:19.380 --> 00:12:21.610 align:middle line:84%
the same quarter
pounder with cheese,

00:12:21.610 --> 00:12:25.100 align:middle line:84%
and this time I'm eating
the bread and not the meat.

00:12:25.100 --> 00:12:26.340 align:middle line:90%
I can't just eat a burger.

00:12:26.340 --> 00:12:29.590 align:middle line:90%


00:12:29.590 --> 00:12:31.880 align:middle line:84%
And my wife at the
time used to joke to me

00:12:31.880 --> 00:12:35.360 align:middle line:84%
that I was on the Atkins diet
during the day and the Pritikin

00:12:35.360 --> 00:12:36.160 align:middle line:90%
diet at night.

00:12:36.160 --> 00:12:38.720 align:middle line:90%


00:12:38.720 --> 00:12:41.870 align:middle line:84%
Because I by the end of the
day, who could go without carbs?

00:12:41.870 --> 00:12:45.320 align:middle line:90%
So I jumped ship.

00:12:45.320 --> 00:12:47.360 align:middle line:90%
That didn't work, by the way.

00:12:47.360 --> 00:12:49.550 align:middle line:10%
I don't recommend that one.

00:12:49.550 --> 00:12:51.960 align:middle line:90%
That's a recipe for disaster.

00:12:51.960 --> 00:12:52.760 align:middle line:90%
But I did that.

00:12:52.760 --> 00:12:54.800 align:middle line:90%
And I had fitness trainers.

00:12:54.800 --> 00:12:55.790 align:middle line:90%
I had homeopaths.

00:12:55.790 --> 00:12:57.110 align:middle line:90%
Doctors.

00:12:57.110 --> 00:12:58.070 align:middle line:90%
I did acupuncture.

00:12:58.070 --> 00:13:00.920 align:middle line:84%
Have you ever done
acupuncture for weight loss?

00:13:00.920 --> 00:13:03.080 align:middle line:84%
Apparently, there's
an acupressure point

00:13:03.080 --> 00:13:05.030 align:middle line:90%
right here on your ear.

00:13:05.030 --> 00:13:08.950 align:middle line:90%
And I had seeds taped to my ear.

00:13:08.950 --> 00:13:11.230 align:middle line:84%
And so the idea is,
whenever you're hungry,

00:13:11.230 --> 00:13:14.650 align:middle line:84%
you're supposed to kind
of rub these seeds,

00:13:14.650 --> 00:13:16.585 align:middle line:84%
and it makes your
hunger go away.

00:13:16.585 --> 00:13:19.240 align:middle line:84%
So I'm walking down the streets
of New York passing the pizza

00:13:19.240 --> 00:13:22.360 align:middle line:84%
places sitting there going
like this rubbing the seeds.

00:13:22.360 --> 00:13:25.250 align:middle line:84%
They think I'm some sort of FBI
surveillance agent, you know?

00:13:25.250 --> 00:13:30.773 align:middle line:84%
Like, he's taking the
pizza out of the oven.

00:13:30.773 --> 00:13:32.440 align:middle line:84%
Looks like it's going
to be a pepperoni.

00:13:32.440 --> 00:13:34.918 align:middle line:90%


00:13:34.918 --> 00:13:36.460 align:middle line:84%
You know, I'm doing
all these things,

00:13:36.460 --> 00:13:37.600 align:middle line:84%
and they all work
in the short term.

00:13:37.600 --> 00:13:38.683 align:middle line:90%
And then, I'd bounce back.

00:13:38.683 --> 00:13:42.150 align:middle line:84%
And it just kept going and going
and going and going like that.

00:13:42.150 --> 00:13:49.560 align:middle line:84%
And this went on until
I gained over 100 kilos.

00:13:49.560 --> 00:13:55.290 align:middle line:84%
Lose five kilos, gain 10 kilos,
lose five kilos, gain 10 kilos.

00:13:55.290 --> 00:13:59.260 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, I looked
something like that.

00:13:59.260 --> 00:14:02.250 align:middle line:90%
That was me in 2001.

00:14:02.250 --> 00:14:05.645 align:middle line:84%
And I had a turning
point back then,

00:14:05.645 --> 00:14:07.020 align:middle line:84%
about a month
after that picture.

00:14:07.020 --> 00:14:09.570 align:middle line:90%


00:14:09.570 --> 00:14:14.220 align:middle line:84%
I remember I was driving home
from a movie in New Jersey,

00:14:14.220 --> 00:14:17.752 align:middle line:84%
and I was thinking
about the last 11 years.

00:14:17.752 --> 00:14:19.710 align:middle line:84%
And I was thinking about,
no matter what I did,

00:14:19.710 --> 00:14:20.627 align:middle line:90%
I kept gaining weight.

00:14:20.627 --> 00:14:24.230 align:middle line:84%
And what was
interesting for me is

00:14:24.230 --> 00:14:28.790 align:middle line:84%
that there was a time that
it wasn't an issue at all.

00:14:28.790 --> 00:14:30.380 align:middle line:84%
There was a time
that I never had

00:14:30.380 --> 00:14:32.610 align:middle line:90%
to think about weight at all.

00:14:32.610 --> 00:14:35.950 align:middle line:90%


00:14:35.950 --> 00:14:39.650 align:middle line:84%
And now, no matter what I'm
doing, I'm gaining weight.

00:14:39.650 --> 00:14:42.740 align:middle line:84%
And I'm really, really
trying to lose weight.

00:14:42.740 --> 00:14:48.130 align:middle line:90%


00:14:48.130 --> 00:14:49.930 align:middle line:84%
And there's this
common stereotype

00:14:49.930 --> 00:14:52.817 align:middle line:84%
that overweight people are just
weak or lazy or overindulgent,

00:14:52.817 --> 00:14:54.025 align:middle line:90%
or they should just eat less.

00:14:54.025 --> 00:14:57.260 align:middle line:90%


00:14:57.260 --> 00:14:59.360 align:middle line:84%
And I've lived
through that, and if I

00:14:59.360 --> 00:15:03.740 align:middle line:84%
have one message to the
world, weight loss is not

00:15:03.740 --> 00:15:05.270 align:middle line:90%
about discipline or willpower.

00:15:05.270 --> 00:15:08.510 align:middle line:84%
And gaining weight is not
because you're weak or lazy.

00:15:08.510 --> 00:15:11.450 align:middle line:84%
There's a legitimate
thing that happens

00:15:11.450 --> 00:15:15.710 align:middle line:84%
in your body, a switch
that turns on that puts you

00:15:15.710 --> 00:15:17.030 align:middle line:90%
into a fat gaining mode.

00:15:17.030 --> 00:15:20.930 align:middle line:84%
And when that switch
is on, your body

00:15:20.930 --> 00:15:25.560 align:middle line:84%
gets transformed into
a fat storage machine.

00:15:25.560 --> 00:15:29.520 align:middle line:90%
It's very physical and chemical.

00:15:29.520 --> 00:15:34.620 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, the number one
expert, the most world renowned

00:15:34.620 --> 00:15:36.035 align:middle line:90%
biochemical expert--

00:15:36.035 --> 00:15:37.410 align:middle line:84%
his name is Dr.
Jeffrey Friedman.

00:15:37.410 --> 00:15:39.705 align:middle line:84%
He's been termed
the Father of Fat.

00:15:39.705 --> 00:15:41.580 align:middle line:84%
It's not the most exciting
term in the world,

00:15:41.580 --> 00:15:42.575 align:middle line:90%
I don't think really.

00:15:42.575 --> 00:15:44.700 align:middle line:84%
I think he deserves better
than that quite frankly.

00:15:44.700 --> 00:15:47.560 align:middle line:84%
But anyway, discoverer
of the hormone leptin,

00:15:47.560 --> 00:15:52.140 align:middle line:84%
which is the most important
hormone as far as weight loss

00:15:52.140 --> 00:15:53.640 align:middle line:84%
and controlling
your body weight--

00:15:53.640 --> 00:15:58.762 align:middle line:84%
has said that obesity
is not about willpower,

00:15:58.762 --> 00:16:00.470 align:middle line:84%
and losing weight is
not about willpower.

00:16:00.470 --> 00:16:03.180 align:middle line:84%
And we've got to
stop blaming people.

00:16:03.180 --> 00:16:06.630 align:middle line:84%
And modern conventional
wisdom or medical wisdom

00:16:06.630 --> 00:16:10.170 align:middle line:90%
doesn't understand that yet.

00:16:10.170 --> 00:16:12.390 align:middle line:84%
I am on a big crusade
right now, and I'm

00:16:12.390 --> 00:16:15.150 align:middle line:84%
getting lots and lots
of positive feedback

00:16:15.150 --> 00:16:16.710 align:middle line:90%
from the medical community.

00:16:16.710 --> 00:16:20.820 align:middle line:84%
I've just been asked to do a
continuing education course

00:16:20.820 --> 00:16:23.740 align:middle line:90%
for doctors in the states.

00:16:23.740 --> 00:16:26.320 align:middle line:84%
There's been a doctor at
the University of Idaho

00:16:26.320 --> 00:16:29.100 align:middle line:84%
who gave a course to
the faculty and staff

00:16:29.100 --> 00:16:30.580 align:middle line:84%
at the medical
school, the Gabriel

00:16:30.580 --> 00:16:33.387 align:middle line:90%
Method of Weight Reduction.

00:16:33.387 --> 00:16:34.970 align:middle line:84%
And I've also been
asked just recently

00:16:34.970 --> 00:16:36.680 align:middle line:84%
to go speak again at the
American Holistic Medical

00:16:36.680 --> 00:16:37.640 align:middle line:90%
Association.

00:16:37.640 --> 00:16:40.430 align:middle line:84%
So doctors are starting
to recognize this

00:16:40.430 --> 00:16:44.150 align:middle line:84%
that chemically, physically,
when your body wants to be fat,

00:16:44.150 --> 00:16:45.560 align:middle line:84%
it will force you
to gain weight.

00:16:45.560 --> 00:16:47.000 align:middle line:90%
Several things happen.

00:16:47.000 --> 00:16:50.870 align:middle line:84%
Number one, your brain stops
listening to your stomach

00:16:50.870 --> 00:16:54.140 align:middle line:90%
when your body wants to be fat.

00:16:54.140 --> 00:16:57.020 align:middle line:84%
Which means that you
can eat and eat and eat,

00:16:57.020 --> 00:16:59.330 align:middle line:84%
and the only way you're
going to stop eating

00:16:59.330 --> 00:17:03.020 align:middle line:84%
is if your stomach can't
handle anymore food.

00:17:03.020 --> 00:17:05.480 align:middle line:84%
And I remember when I
was in that situation

00:17:05.480 --> 00:17:07.539 align:middle line:84%
that every time after
every meal, I was just--

00:17:07.539 --> 00:17:08.339 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't.

00:17:08.339 --> 00:17:09.240 align:middle line:90%
I was bloated.

00:17:09.240 --> 00:17:10.055 align:middle line:90%
I was stuffed.

00:17:10.055 --> 00:17:11.930 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if you've
ever had that feeling.

00:17:11.930 --> 00:17:14.089 align:middle line:84%
But that's because your
brain is intentionally not

00:17:14.089 --> 00:17:15.050 align:middle line:90%
listening to your stomach.

00:17:15.050 --> 00:17:16.700 align:middle line:84%
It wants you to eat
as much as possible

00:17:16.700 --> 00:17:20.560 align:middle line:90%
when your fat switch is on.

00:17:20.560 --> 00:17:23.050 align:middle line:84%
Your tongue loses its
sensitivity to sweet foods,

00:17:23.050 --> 00:17:25.660 align:middle line:84%
so it causes you to
crave sweeter foods.

00:17:25.660 --> 00:17:27.609 align:middle line:84%
Your metabolism slows
down, and your body

00:17:27.609 --> 00:17:29.050 align:middle line:90%
goes into fat storage mode.

00:17:29.050 --> 00:17:30.670 align:middle line:84%
When you combine
all these things

00:17:30.670 --> 00:17:33.610 align:middle line:84%
in a world of excess,
unlimited empty carbs

00:17:33.610 --> 00:17:37.750 align:middle line:84%
and nutritionally barren food,
it's a recipe for disaster.

00:17:37.750 --> 00:17:39.550 align:middle line:90%
And that's what's happening.

00:17:39.550 --> 00:17:41.015 align:middle line:84%
It's not that
you're weak or lazy.

00:17:41.015 --> 00:17:44.680 align:middle line:90%


00:17:44.680 --> 00:17:48.250 align:middle line:84%
And the same part of the
brain that controls hunger

00:17:48.250 --> 00:17:53.400 align:middle line:84%
controls how much sleep we need
and how much oxygen we need.

00:17:53.400 --> 00:17:55.590 align:middle line:84%
So imagine you
went to your doctor

00:17:55.590 --> 00:17:57.480 align:middle line:84%
and he said, you
know, your problem is

00:17:57.480 --> 00:17:59.480 align:middle line:90%
just you sleep too much.

00:17:59.480 --> 00:18:01.380 align:middle line:90%
Just sleep less.

00:18:01.380 --> 00:18:04.300 align:middle line:84%
You could do that for
a while, couldn't you?

00:18:04.300 --> 00:18:05.922 align:middle line:84%
He says, just sleep
two hours a day.

00:18:05.922 --> 00:18:08.130 align:middle line:84%
And the whole world judged
you, because you were lazy

00:18:08.130 --> 00:18:09.850 align:middle line:84%
because you slept
seven hours a day.

00:18:09.850 --> 00:18:11.087 align:middle line:90%
Just sleep two hours a day.

00:18:11.087 --> 00:18:12.420 align:middle line:90%
So you could do that for awhile.

00:18:12.420 --> 00:18:15.760 align:middle line:84%
You could do it
for a week, maybe.

00:18:15.760 --> 00:18:18.020 align:middle line:10%
10 days at the most.

00:18:18.020 --> 00:18:20.080 align:middle line:90%
But then what would happen?

00:18:20.080 --> 00:18:21.990 align:middle line:84%
Your body would
force you to sleep,

00:18:21.990 --> 00:18:24.120 align:middle line:84%
because it has the
ability to do that.

00:18:24.120 --> 00:18:28.620 align:middle line:90%


00:18:28.620 --> 00:18:31.050 align:middle line:84%
And if you tried to hold
your breath long enough,

00:18:31.050 --> 00:18:33.260 align:middle line:84%
your body would
force you to breathe.

00:18:33.260 --> 00:18:37.000 align:middle line:90%
It's the same with food.

00:18:37.000 --> 00:18:39.040 align:middle line:84%
Your body has the
ability to force

00:18:39.040 --> 00:18:41.410 align:middle line:90%
you to eat sooner or later.

00:18:41.410 --> 00:18:43.797 align:middle line:90%


00:18:43.797 --> 00:18:45.380 align:middle line:84%
So the next time you
go to your doctor

00:18:45.380 --> 00:18:48.420 align:middle line:84%
and he tells you to
eat less, you can just

00:18:48.420 --> 00:18:51.830 align:middle line:90%
tell him to breathe less.

00:18:51.830 --> 00:18:54.410 align:middle line:84%
Because it's the
exact same thing.

00:18:54.410 --> 00:18:55.577 align:middle line:90%
And that's what's happening.

00:18:55.577 --> 00:18:57.785 align:middle line:84%
People are saying eat less
when they don't understand

00:18:57.785 --> 00:18:59.420 align:middle line:84%
that your body is
forcing you to eat,

00:18:59.420 --> 00:19:00.740 align:middle line:90%
and I have lived through it.

00:19:00.740 --> 00:19:04.230 align:middle line:84%
And now, I've been on
the other side of it.

00:19:04.230 --> 00:19:06.540 align:middle line:84%
And now, it's been six,
almost seven years.

00:19:06.540 --> 00:19:08.760 align:middle line:90%
I never think about dieting.

00:19:08.760 --> 00:19:10.050 align:middle line:90%
Not once.

00:19:10.050 --> 00:19:12.450 align:middle line:84%
People that are around me
are amazed at how much I eat.

00:19:12.450 --> 00:19:13.325 align:middle line:90%
And you can ask them.

00:19:13.325 --> 00:19:15.720 align:middle line:84%
Jackson around here and
everyone that we sit with,

00:19:15.720 --> 00:19:16.830 align:middle line:90%
I eat what I want.

00:19:16.830 --> 00:19:18.555 align:middle line:84%
I do eat a very healthy
diet, but I never

00:19:18.555 --> 00:19:19.680 align:middle line:90%
have to think about weight.

00:19:19.680 --> 00:19:21.690 align:middle line:84%
There's never a time I say I'm
not going to have something.

00:19:21.690 --> 00:19:22.490 align:middle line:90%
Never.

00:19:22.490 --> 00:19:24.890 align:middle line:90%
Not in seven years, almost.

00:19:24.890 --> 00:19:26.893 align:middle line:84%
And that's because the
issue's been dealt with.

00:19:26.893 --> 00:19:28.810 align:middle line:84%
My body's no longer
forcing me to gain weight.

00:19:28.810 --> 00:19:33.450 align:middle line:90%


00:19:33.450 --> 00:19:39.010 align:middle line:84%
So yes, so I had the
turning point back in 2001.

00:19:39.010 --> 00:19:42.580 align:middle line:84%
And I spent a lot of time
doing research on the internet.

00:19:42.580 --> 00:19:47.020 align:middle line:84%
What I decided was, I decided I
was never going to diet again.

00:19:47.020 --> 00:19:50.395 align:middle line:90%


00:19:50.395 --> 00:19:52.020 align:middle line:84%
Because what's the
point if your body's

00:19:52.020 --> 00:19:53.783 align:middle line:90%
forcing you to gain weight?

00:19:53.783 --> 00:19:55.200 align:middle line:84%
And I decided,
rather than diet, I

00:19:55.200 --> 00:19:58.260 align:middle line:84%
was going to try to figure
out why my body wanted

00:19:58.260 --> 00:20:00.990 align:middle line:84%
to be a fat in the
first place and what

00:20:00.990 --> 00:20:03.480 align:middle line:84%
I could do to get it
to want to be thin.

00:20:03.480 --> 00:20:05.550 align:middle line:84%
And I had a very solid
biochemistry background

00:20:05.550 --> 00:20:07.050 align:middle line:84%
from the University
of Pennsylvania,

00:20:07.050 --> 00:20:08.730 align:middle line:84%
and that gave me
enough of a foundation

00:20:08.730 --> 00:20:10.320 align:middle line:84%
to do the research
on the internet.

00:20:10.320 --> 00:20:13.140 align:middle line:84%
And I spent hours and hours
a day studying biochemistry.

00:20:13.140 --> 00:20:15.950 align:middle line:90%


00:20:15.950 --> 00:20:19.570 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I discovered
this fat switch that we have,

00:20:19.570 --> 00:20:21.830 align:middle line:90%
or what I call the fat programs.

00:20:21.830 --> 00:20:24.140 align:middle line:84%
And I put together
an approach for me

00:20:24.140 --> 00:20:27.680 align:middle line:84%
that worked at dealing with
my issues that were activating

00:20:27.680 --> 00:20:29.390 align:middle line:90%
my fat programs.

00:20:29.390 --> 00:20:31.280 align:middle line:90%
And I started to lose weight.

00:20:31.280 --> 00:20:33.800 align:middle line:84%
And what's interesting is,
I didn't lose weight quickly

00:20:33.800 --> 00:20:34.670 align:middle line:90%
in the beginning.

00:20:34.670 --> 00:20:38.540 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't like a diet, where
you lose 20 kilos in 20 days

00:20:38.540 --> 00:20:40.580 align:middle line:84%
and then you had this
big old rebound thing.

00:20:40.580 --> 00:20:41.450 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't like that.

00:20:41.450 --> 00:20:43.100 align:middle line:84%
I lost weight slowly
in the beginning.

00:20:43.100 --> 00:20:48.720 align:middle line:84%
I lost about 25 kilos
over a six month period.

00:20:48.720 --> 00:20:50.960 align:middle line:84%
So it's like a kilo
a week or something.

00:20:50.960 --> 00:20:55.130 align:middle line:84%
And when you're over 180
kilos or over 400 pounds,

00:20:55.130 --> 00:20:57.740 align:middle line:90%
that's not setting any records.

00:20:57.740 --> 00:21:01.200 align:middle line:84%
That's not going to get
you on Biggest Loser.

00:21:01.200 --> 00:21:04.020 align:middle line:84%
If I'd ever want to
be on Biggest Loser.

00:21:04.020 --> 00:21:07.680 align:middle line:84%
But what happened
is, I wasn't dieting.

00:21:07.680 --> 00:21:09.870 align:middle line:84%
I was making sure that I
was nourishing my body,

00:21:09.870 --> 00:21:12.200 align:middle line:84%
and I was dealing with
the stresses in my life

00:21:12.200 --> 00:21:14.730 align:middle line:84%
that were activating
my fat programs.

00:21:14.730 --> 00:21:16.470 align:middle line:84%
And I started to
become less hungry.

00:21:16.470 --> 00:21:18.030 align:middle line:90%
But I still craved chocolate.

00:21:18.030 --> 00:21:20.252 align:middle line:90%
I still craved junk food.

00:21:20.252 --> 00:21:21.210 align:middle line:90%
And whenever I wanted--

00:21:21.210 --> 00:21:23.418 align:middle line:84%
I used to keep these chocolate
almonds in the fridge.

00:21:23.418 --> 00:21:25.670 align:middle line:84%
And whenever I wanted
one, I'd just have one.

00:21:25.670 --> 00:21:26.670 align:middle line:90%
There was no hesitation.

00:21:26.670 --> 00:21:28.500 align:middle line:90%
Not the slightest hesitation.

00:21:28.500 --> 00:21:31.020 align:middle line:84%
Before, there was always
a good day and a bad day.

00:21:31.020 --> 00:21:33.035 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know if
you've ever lived this,

00:21:33.035 --> 00:21:34.410 align:middle line:84%
but people live
their whole lives

00:21:34.410 --> 00:21:36.580 align:middle line:84%
where every single day is
a good day and a bad day.

00:21:36.580 --> 00:21:38.760 align:middle line:84%
It's a battle from
the moment you get up.

00:21:38.760 --> 00:21:41.100 align:middle line:84%
Today, you wake up and it's
going to be a good day.

00:21:41.100 --> 00:21:42.600 align:middle line:84%
You know, you have
your fruit juice,

00:21:42.600 --> 00:21:45.090 align:middle line:84%
and you have your Weetabix, or
you have your whatever it is.

00:21:45.090 --> 00:21:47.550 align:middle line:84%
And then around 11:00, you get
these cravings for chocolate

00:21:47.550 --> 00:21:49.542 align:middle line:90%
or whatever it is, or a donut.

00:21:49.542 --> 00:21:50.500 align:middle line:90%
And today's a good day.

00:21:50.500 --> 00:21:51.710 align:middle line:90%
You're not going to do that.

00:21:51.710 --> 00:21:53.010 align:middle line:90%
And you gut it out.

00:21:53.010 --> 00:21:54.900 align:middle line:84%
And then you get to
lunch, and you're OK.

00:21:54.900 --> 00:21:57.210 align:middle line:84%
And it then by the time
it's 4:00, you're exhausted,

00:21:57.210 --> 00:21:58.530 align:middle line:90%
and somebody yelled at you.

00:21:58.530 --> 00:22:00.060 align:middle line:90%
And you're like, oh, screw it.

00:22:00.060 --> 00:22:01.955 align:middle line:84%
And then all of a
sudden, it's a bad day.

00:22:01.955 --> 00:22:04.080 align:middle line:84%
And you go to the store,
and you buy all the things

00:22:04.080 --> 00:22:06.300 align:middle line:84%
that you've been staring
at for the last two weeks.

00:22:06.300 --> 00:22:07.590 align:middle line:90%
You take it home.

00:22:07.590 --> 00:22:09.510 align:middle line:84%
Next thing you know,
it's 2:00 in the morning,

00:22:09.510 --> 00:22:11.820 align:middle line:84%
and there's pizza
containers on the floor,

00:22:11.820 --> 00:22:14.510 align:middle line:84%
and your hands are orange
from cheese twists,

00:22:14.510 --> 00:22:17.830 align:middle line:84%
and you've got cupcake
wrappers everywhere.

00:22:17.830 --> 00:22:18.630 align:middle line:90%
Boom.

00:22:18.630 --> 00:22:20.340 align:middle line:90%
Bad day.

00:22:20.340 --> 00:22:21.960 align:middle line:90%
And then, you start again.

00:22:21.960 --> 00:22:22.760 align:middle line:90%
Tomorrow, OK.

00:22:22.760 --> 00:22:24.310 align:middle line:90%
We're going to start fresh.

00:22:24.310 --> 00:22:26.453 align:middle line:90%
So I lived this way.

00:22:26.453 --> 00:22:27.870 align:middle line:84%
Every day was a
good day and bad--

00:22:27.870 --> 00:22:28.670 align:middle line:90%
I stopped that.

00:22:28.670 --> 00:22:30.780 align:middle line:84%
There was no more good
days, no more bad days.

00:22:30.780 --> 00:22:32.697 align:middle line:84%
If I wanted a piece of
chocolate, I'd have it.

00:22:32.697 --> 00:22:33.650 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:22:33.650 --> 00:22:34.300 align:middle line:90%
And I'd keep walking.

00:22:34.300 --> 00:22:36.342 align:middle line:84%
I just thought, it's
chemicals in, chemicals out.

00:22:36.342 --> 00:22:37.890 align:middle line:84%
If I wanted another
one, I'd take it.

00:22:37.890 --> 00:22:39.570 align:middle line:84%
But I made sure I
nourished my body.

00:22:39.570 --> 00:22:43.390 align:middle line:90%


00:22:43.390 --> 00:22:46.120 align:middle line:84%
And I made sure I dealt with the
stresses that were activating

00:22:46.120 --> 00:22:47.140 align:middle line:90%
the fat programs.

00:22:47.140 --> 00:22:47.970 align:middle line:84%
And the weight
started to come off.

00:22:47.970 --> 00:22:50.440 align:middle line:84%
But what was interesting
is, after about six months,

00:22:50.440 --> 00:22:53.020 align:middle line:84%
rather than have that
plateau, the weight

00:22:53.020 --> 00:22:54.770 align:middle line:90%
actually came off faster.

00:22:54.770 --> 00:22:56.720 align:middle line:84%
And I discovered there's
a reason for that.

00:22:56.720 --> 00:22:59.110 align:middle line:84%
And that is, when your body
actually wants to be thin--

00:22:59.110 --> 00:23:02.068 align:middle line:84%
that is not when you force
yourself to lose weight,

00:23:02.068 --> 00:23:04.360 align:middle line:84%
but when you actually get
your body to want to be thin,

00:23:04.360 --> 00:23:06.250 align:middle line:84%
it becomes very
efficient at burning fat.

00:23:06.250 --> 00:23:09.060 align:middle line:90%


00:23:09.060 --> 00:23:11.967 align:middle line:84%
You become more of a
fat burning machine,

00:23:11.967 --> 00:23:13.800 align:middle line:84%
and you can lose weight
quicker and quicker.

00:23:13.800 --> 00:23:16.680 align:middle line:84%
Right up to the end,
I was losing weight

00:23:16.680 --> 00:23:18.450 align:middle line:84%
at maybe two or
three kilos a day.

00:23:18.450 --> 00:23:20.190 align:middle line:84%
Those last couple of
kilos, the last 10

00:23:20.190 --> 00:23:22.710 align:middle line:84%
kilos that most people say
are impossible to lose,

00:23:22.710 --> 00:23:25.230 align:middle line:84%
when you lose that much
weight, it flew off me.

00:23:25.230 --> 00:23:27.450 align:middle line:84%
My body just didn't
want the weight anymore.

00:23:27.450 --> 00:23:28.620 align:middle line:90%
The issues were done.

00:23:28.620 --> 00:23:30.160 align:middle line:90%
The problem was resolved.

00:23:30.160 --> 00:23:31.080 align:middle line:90%
It was gone.

00:23:31.080 --> 00:23:32.890 align:middle line:90%
End of story.

00:23:32.890 --> 00:23:34.390 align:middle line:84%
And when your body
wants to be thin,

00:23:34.390 --> 00:23:37.630 align:middle line:84%
it becomes very
efficient at burning fat.

00:23:37.630 --> 00:23:42.040 align:middle line:84%
And so the whole time I was
doing this, I was taking notes.

00:23:42.040 --> 00:23:43.090 align:middle line:90%
I was writing.

00:23:43.090 --> 00:23:44.740 align:middle line:84%
And I was never a
writer, by the way.

00:23:44.740 --> 00:23:46.270 align:middle line:90%
I always hated writing.

00:23:46.270 --> 00:23:48.820 align:middle line:84%
Like at uni-- I spent
five years at uni,

00:23:48.820 --> 00:23:50.740 align:middle line:84%
and I took everything
from biochemistry

00:23:50.740 --> 00:23:52.070 align:middle line:90%
to economics to photography.

00:23:52.070 --> 00:23:52.870 align:middle line:90%
It didn't matter.

00:23:52.870 --> 00:23:54.040 align:middle line:90%
I'd take any course.

00:23:54.040 --> 00:23:56.670 align:middle line:84%
My only criteria
was that I wouldn't

00:23:56.670 --> 00:23:58.920 align:middle line:90%
have to write anything.

00:23:58.920 --> 00:24:01.600 align:middle line:84%
And I only had to
take two courses

00:24:01.600 --> 00:24:03.730 align:middle line:90%
where I had to write a paper.

00:24:03.730 --> 00:24:05.200 align:middle line:90%
One was English.

00:24:05.200 --> 00:24:06.700 align:middle line:84%
I had to take a
semester of English.

00:24:06.700 --> 00:24:08.530 align:middle line:84%
And the other was
a management course

00:24:08.530 --> 00:24:10.210 align:middle line:84%
that was supposed to
be a guaranteed A.

00:24:10.210 --> 00:24:13.110 align:middle line:84%
And I was the only
person I have ever heard

00:24:13.110 --> 00:24:14.360 align:middle line:90%
of that got a B in that class.

00:24:14.360 --> 00:24:17.780 align:middle line:90%


00:24:17.780 --> 00:24:19.257 align:middle line:90%
I just didn't like writing.

00:24:19.257 --> 00:24:20.840 align:middle line:84%
But all of a sudden,
what would happen

00:24:20.840 --> 00:24:24.920 align:middle line:84%
is, I used to sit every
morning, I'd do this meditation.

00:24:24.920 --> 00:24:27.330 align:middle line:84%
And I'd get to a certain
point of the meditation,

00:24:27.330 --> 00:24:28.130 align:middle line:90%
and then, boom.

00:24:28.130 --> 00:24:30.020 align:middle line:84%
In an instant, all
of this information

00:24:30.020 --> 00:24:30.920 align:middle line:90%
would come out of me.

00:24:30.920 --> 00:24:32.050 align:middle line:90%
Like boom.

00:24:32.050 --> 00:24:33.592 align:middle line:84%
I'd get all this
information, and I'd

00:24:33.592 --> 00:24:34.748 align:middle line:90%
write for like 30 pages.

00:24:34.748 --> 00:24:36.290 align:middle line:84%
And then, I'd sit
and meditate again.

00:24:36.290 --> 00:24:37.550 align:middle line:84%
I'd get to a certain
point, and boom,

00:24:37.550 --> 00:24:38.850 align:middle line:90%
I'd get all this information.

00:24:38.850 --> 00:24:40.600 align:middle line:84%
I'd start writing and
writing and writing.

00:24:40.600 --> 00:24:44.870 align:middle line:84%
And I had this 60 or 90 pages
of stuff, of information.

00:24:44.870 --> 00:24:47.867 align:middle line:10%
And then, I transcribed it
on the computer, information

00:24:47.867 --> 00:24:50.450 align:middle line:10%
about weight loss, about the way
the body works, the mind body

00:24:50.450 --> 00:24:53.240 align:middle line:10%
connection, visualizations.

00:24:53.240 --> 00:24:56.450 align:middle line:10%
I had this big old
document I used

00:24:56.450 --> 00:24:59.230 align:middle line:10%
to call Weight Loss and
the Meaning of Life.

00:24:59.230 --> 00:25:01.050 align:middle line:84%
And it was like
millions of words.

00:25:01.050 --> 00:25:03.220 align:middle line:84%
And after I lost the way,
I sort of put it together.

00:25:03.220 --> 00:25:04.020 align:middle line:90%
I said, OK.

00:25:04.020 --> 00:25:05.310 align:middle line:90%
What is it that I'm saying?

00:25:05.310 --> 00:25:08.910 align:middle line:84%
And I put together all
the different categories

00:25:08.910 --> 00:25:10.980 align:middle line:90%
of the approach.

00:25:10.980 --> 00:25:15.090 align:middle line:84%
And after that, also, I
was on TV very quickly.

00:25:15.090 --> 00:25:19.500 align:middle line:84%
I sent my before and after
pictures to The Today Show,

00:25:19.500 --> 00:25:21.570 align:middle line:90%
you know, Today Tonight.

00:25:21.570 --> 00:25:23.430 align:middle line:90%
I emailed it to them.

00:25:23.430 --> 00:25:25.995 align:middle line:84%
And 10 minutes later,
they called me.

00:25:25.995 --> 00:25:28.120 align:middle line:84%
I thought maybe in a couple
of months, they'd call.

00:25:28.120 --> 00:25:29.700 align:middle line:90%
10 minutes later, they call me.

00:25:29.700 --> 00:25:30.825 align:middle line:90%
And I'm talking to them.

00:25:30.825 --> 00:25:31.950 align:middle line:90%
And they say, that's great.

00:25:31.950 --> 00:25:34.600 align:middle line:90%
We'll be right there.

00:25:34.600 --> 00:25:35.850 align:middle line:90%
I said, you'll be right where?

00:25:35.850 --> 00:25:37.642 align:middle line:84%
They said, we're coming
over to your house.

00:25:37.642 --> 00:25:39.600 align:middle line:84%
I said, I live in Denmark,
Western Australia.

00:25:39.600 --> 00:25:41.640 align:middle line:84%
I'm 500 kilometers
south of Perth.

00:25:41.640 --> 00:25:42.815 align:middle line:90%
They said, that's all right.

00:25:42.815 --> 00:25:43.690 align:middle line:90%
We have a helicopter.

00:25:43.690 --> 00:25:45.607 align:middle line:84%
We're going to be there
in an hour and a half.

00:25:45.607 --> 00:25:47.640 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:25:47.640 --> 00:25:49.220 align:middle line:90%
I had to go tell my wife--

00:25:49.220 --> 00:25:50.590 align:middle line:90%
I had a little two-year-old kid.

00:25:50.590 --> 00:25:52.160 align:middle line:90%
The house is a mess.

00:25:52.160 --> 00:25:54.840 align:middle line:84%
When you have a
kid, you're not--

00:25:54.840 --> 00:25:56.303 align:middle line:84%
my wife was a very
private person.

00:25:56.303 --> 00:25:58.470 align:middle line:84%
And I had to tell her that
there was a national film

00:25:58.470 --> 00:26:01.355 align:middle line:84%
crew coming in an hour
and a half to talk to us.

00:26:01.355 --> 00:26:02.730 align:middle line:84%
It took me an hour
and 15 minutes

00:26:02.730 --> 00:26:05.860 align:middle line:84%
to convince her that I
wasn't lying, in which case,

00:26:05.860 --> 00:26:06.660 align:middle line:90%
she said, right.

00:26:06.660 --> 00:26:07.570 align:middle line:90%
I'm out of here.

00:26:07.570 --> 00:26:08.370 align:middle line:90%
Left.

00:26:08.370 --> 00:26:10.280 align:middle line:90%
Left me with this big old mess.

00:26:10.280 --> 00:26:11.610 align:middle line:84%
I'm sitting there taking
clothes and putting them

00:26:11.610 --> 00:26:13.500 align:middle line:84%
in the washing machine,
hiding them anywhere

00:26:13.500 --> 00:26:15.973 align:middle line:84%
I can, just to kind
of create a place.

00:26:15.973 --> 00:26:18.390 align:middle line:84%
And then they come over, and
we do all this big old thing.

00:26:18.390 --> 00:26:19.848 align:middle line:84%
And then the next
thing I know, I'm

00:26:19.848 --> 00:26:21.952 align:middle line:84%
getting calls from
people all over.

00:26:21.952 --> 00:26:23.660 align:middle line:84%
And I'm seeing patterns
that are similar,

00:26:23.660 --> 00:26:24.830 align:middle line:90%
and I'm working with them.

00:26:24.830 --> 00:26:26.960 align:middle line:84%
And I'm seeing a lot of
things that I had but then

00:26:26.960 --> 00:26:29.090 align:middle line:84%
a lot of things that I
didn't have but still

00:26:29.090 --> 00:26:32.240 align:middle line:84%
apply to the basic principles
of what's causing your body

00:26:32.240 --> 00:26:34.640 align:middle line:90%
to want to be fat or thin.

00:26:34.640 --> 00:26:37.620 align:middle line:84%
And I systematized it
and put it together

00:26:37.620 --> 00:26:41.215 align:middle line:84%
in an approach that
applies to everybody.

00:26:41.215 --> 00:26:43.590 align:middle line:84%
And so that's what we're going
to be talking about today.

00:26:43.590 --> 00:26:45.757 align:middle line:84%
We're going to be talking
about how to get your body

00:26:45.757 --> 00:26:48.770 align:middle line:84%
to want to be thin, how to
resolve the issue forever,

00:26:48.770 --> 00:26:51.770 align:middle line:84%
how to have an approach so
that when you walk out of here,

00:26:51.770 --> 00:26:54.950 align:middle line:84%
you're going to know exactly
