Too much sun is a stress.

00:28:02.050 --> 00:28:06.460 align:middle line:84%
And by the way, a
stress is anything

00:28:06.460 --> 00:28:08.980 align:middle line:84%
that causes your body
to be alert to the fact

00:28:08.980 --> 00:28:12.400 align:middle line:84%
that there may be
a threat out there.

00:28:12.400 --> 00:28:14.170 align:middle line:84%
The threat could be
a tiger chasing you.

00:28:14.170 --> 00:28:15.790 align:middle line:84%
The threat could be
starving to death.

00:28:15.790 --> 00:28:17.457 align:middle line:84%
The threat could be
getting skin cancer.

00:28:17.457 --> 00:28:19.950 align:middle line:84%
Whatever the threat
is, that's a stress.

00:28:19.950 --> 00:28:21.730 align:middle line:90%
A stress is like an alarm bell.

00:28:21.730 --> 00:28:23.658 align:middle line:84%
So let's say you got
go out in the sun,

00:28:23.658 --> 00:28:24.700 align:middle line:90%
and you get too much sun.

00:28:24.700 --> 00:28:27.610 align:middle line:90%


