Let me have two--

00:38:05.530 --> 00:38:07.740 align:middle line:84%
I can finish that in
30-- you can't even

00:38:07.740 --> 00:38:09.490 align:middle line:84%
focus on the conversation,
because they've

00:38:09.490 --> 00:38:11.410 align:middle line:84%
got this gorgeous
pizza, and you've

00:38:11.410 --> 00:38:14.710 align:middle line:84%
got your fat-free,
wheat-free Weetabix, whatever

00:38:14.710 --> 00:38:16.300 align:middle line:90%
you're eating.

00:38:16.300 --> 00:38:18.730 align:middle line:84%
Burger without the bread and
bread without the burger.

00:38:18.730 --> 00:38:19.120 align:middle line:90%
Whatever.

00:38:19.120 --> 00:38:20.590 align:middle line:84%
And they're having
their milkshake,

00:38:20.590 --> 00:38:21.310 align:middle line:90%
and they're talking to you.

00:38:21.310 --> 00:38:23.268 align:middle line:84%
And they're really engaged
in the conversation.

00:38:23.268 --> 00:38:25.330 align:middle line:84%
You can't listen to a
word they're saying.

00:38:25.330 --> 00:38:29.090 align:middle line:90%
You know, just, what?

00:38:29.090 --> 00:38:31.693 align:middle line:90%
Because their brain's listening.

00:38:31.693 --> 00:38:33.610 align:middle line:84%
Their brain starts to
listen to their stomach.

00:38:33.610 --> 00:38:35.880 align:middle line:90%
Their metabolism speeds up.

00:38:35.880 --> 00:38:38.360 align:middle line:90%
And they want to be active.

00:38:38.360 --> 00:38:40.235 align:middle line:84%
And this is because
that survival program

00:38:40.235 --> 00:38:41.180 align:middle line:90%
is being activated.

00:38:41.180 --> 00:38:42.890 align:middle line:84%
And what's interesting
about stress--

00:38:42.890 --> 00:38:45.027 align:middle line:84%
and nobody's ever been
able to explain this,

00:38:45.027 --> 00:38:46.610 align:middle line:84%
and I'm sure you've
all noticed this--

00:38:46.610 --> 00:38:48.950 align:middle line:84%
is the same stress will
make one person fatter

00:38:48.950 --> 00:38:52.180 align:middle line:90%
and another person thinner.

00:38:52.180 --> 00:38:54.527 align:middle line:84%
You know those people,
they get stressed

00:38:54.527 --> 00:38:56.110 align:middle line:84%
and they start losing
all that weight?

00:38:56.110 --> 00:38:57.070 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I'm so stressed.

00:38:57.070 --> 00:38:58.812 align:middle line:90%
I can't eat anything.

00:38:58.812 --> 00:39:00.520 align:middle line:84%
You know, they just
lose all that weight.

00:39:00.520 --> 00:39:01.540 align:middle line:90%
You're like, great.

00:39:01.540 --> 00:39:02.340 align:middle line:90%
Good for you.

00:39:02.340 --> 00:39:04.486 align:middle line:90%
I'm so sorry to hear that.

00:39:04.486 --> 00:39:06.100 align:middle line:90%
You know what I'm talking about?

00:39:06.100 --> 00:39:08.430 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I can't eat anything.

00:39:08.430 --> 00:39:10.540 align:middle line:84%
It's because it's activating
a different survival

00:39:10.540 --> 00:39:12.150 align:middle line:90%
program inside their brain.

00:39:12.150 --> 00:39:14.890 align:middle line:90%


00:39:14.890 --> 00:39:16.270 align:middle line:90%
It's the same stress.

00:39:16.270 --> 00:39:18.160 align:middle line:90%
Different adaptation.

00:39:18.160 --> 00:39:19.300 align:middle line:90%
Different program.

00:39:19.300 --> 00:39:21.760 align:middle line:84%
And I remember when I was
working on Wall Street,

00:39:21.760 --> 00:39:23.810 align:middle line:90%
I had a business partner.

00:39:23.810 --> 00:39:25.390 align:middle line:90%
And we worked in the same desk.

00:39:25.390 --> 00:39:28.030 align:middle line:84%
He was right on the
other side of me.

00:39:28.030 --> 00:39:30.160 align:middle line:84%
And we worked
together for 11 years.

00:39:30.160 --> 00:39:32.148 align:middle line:84%
And the whole time I
was working with him,

00:39:32.148 --> 00:39:33.940 align:middle line:84%
I was getting fatter
and fatter and fatter,

00:39:33.940 --> 00:39:37.080 align:middle line:84%
and he was getting thinner
and thinner and thinner.

00:39:37.080 --> 00:39:40.710 align:middle line:84%
And this guy used to order
milkshakes for lunch.

00:39:40.710 --> 00:39:43.380 align:middle line:84%
He'd call up and they'd go,
uh, what will you have today?

00:39:43.380 --> 00:39:45.062 align:middle line:84%
Uh, I think I'll
have a milkshake.

00:39:45.062 --> 00:39:46.770 align:middle line:84%
And he'd have this
milkshake on his desk,

00:39:46.770 --> 00:39:47.520 align:middle line:90%
and he'd have a couple of sips.

00:39:47.520 --> 00:39:48.300 align:middle line:90%
It'd be sitting there.

00:39:48.300 --> 00:39:50.675 align:middle line:84%
And I'd be ordering my hamburger
without the bun one week

00:39:50.675 --> 00:39:53.008 align:middle line:84%
and my bun without the
hamburger the next week.

00:39:53.008 --> 00:39:54.425 align:middle line:84%
And I'd be trying
to work, and I'd

00:39:54.425 --> 00:39:55.967 align:middle line:84%
be staring at his
milkshake thinking,

00:39:55.967 --> 00:39:58.105 align:middle line:90%
if I could just have 30 seconds.

00:39:58.105 --> 00:39:58.980 align:middle line:90%
Suck that thing down.

00:39:58.980 --> 00:40:01.740 align:middle line:90%
Get a big old brain freeze.

00:40:01.740 --> 00:40:03.280 align:middle line:84%
And it would just
be sitting there.

00:40:03.280 --> 00:40:06.370 align:middle line:84%
And he was getting
thinner and thinner.

00:40:06.370 --> 00:40:09.040 align:middle line:84%
But what was different
about him than me is the way

00:40:09.040 --> 00:40:10.820 align:middle line:90%
he reacted to stress.

00:40:10.820 --> 00:40:14.490 align:middle line:84%
See, whenever things
went wrong in the office,

00:40:14.490 --> 00:40:17.560 align:middle line:84%
I would just sort of just
sit there and just take it.

00:40:17.560 --> 00:40:22.430 align:middle line:90%


00:40:22.430 --> 00:40:25.490 align:middle line:84%
Which, when you think about
it, is very similar to the way

00:40:25.490 --> 00:40:28.910 align:middle line:90%
you would react in a famine.

00:40:28.910 --> 00:40:31.730 align:middle line:84%
If you're in a famine, you
can't run away from it.

00:40:31.730 --> 00:40:33.050 align:middle line:90%
You can't fight it.

00:40:33.050 --> 00:40:35.000 align:middle line:90%
You just have to take it.

00:40:35.000 --> 00:40:37.850 align:middle line:84%
You have to just
sort of slow down.

00:40:37.850 --> 00:40:39.290 align:middle line:90%
That's what I did.

00:40:39.290 --> 00:40:41.570 align:middle line:90%
I just took it.

00:40:41.570 --> 00:40:43.070 align:middle line:90%
I just sort of slowed down.

00:40:43.070 --> 00:40:46.600 align:middle line:90%


00:40:46.600 --> 00:40:49.810 align:middle line:84%
But this guy, the slightest
thing that would go wrong,

00:40:49.810 --> 00:40:51.640 align:middle line:90%
and he would flail his arms.

00:40:51.640 --> 00:40:54.490 align:middle line:84%
The fax machine wouldn't work,
and he'd throw the fax machine

00:40:54.490 --> 00:40:55.290 align:middle line:90%
on the ground.

00:40:55.290 --> 00:40:56.400 align:middle line:90%
He'd go, fuck.

00:40:56.400 --> 00:40:59.002 align:middle line:84%
Bernard, we need another
fucking fax machine.

00:40:59.002 --> 00:41:03.160 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:41:03.160 --> 00:41:05.320 align:middle line:84%
And I'd say to him,
well, Dave, Bernard's

00:41:05.320 --> 00:41:07.188 align:middle line:90%
getting another fax machine.

00:41:07.188 --> 00:41:08.980 align:middle line:84%
But the next time that
happens, if you just

00:41:08.980 --> 00:41:13.232 align:middle line:84%
press that green button,
that's the start button.

00:41:13.232 --> 00:41:15.290 align:middle line:90%
It shouldn't happen again.

00:41:15.290 --> 00:41:20.100 align:middle line:90%


00:41:20.100 --> 00:41:20.960 align:middle line:90%
But everything.

00:41:20.960 --> 00:41:21.760 align:middle line:90%
He would react.

00:41:21.760 --> 00:41:23.460 align:middle line:90%
It was like he was in a battle.

00:41:23.460 --> 00:41:25.890 align:middle line:90%
It's like he was in a war.

00:41:25.890 --> 00:41:30.060 align:middle line:84%
And so we're sitting at the
same desk doing the same job

00:41:30.060 --> 00:41:32.070 align:middle line:90%
and the same stress.

00:41:32.070 --> 00:41:35.400 align:middle line:84%
But to my body, it was like
I was in an arctic wasteland

00:41:35.400 --> 00:41:37.170 align:middle line:90%
starving to death.

00:41:37.170 --> 00:41:39.690 align:middle line:84%
And to his body, he was in the
African Savannah fighting off

00:41:39.690 --> 00:41:41.350 align:middle line:90%
tigers left and right.

00:41:41.350 --> 00:41:42.150 align:middle line:90%
Lions.

00:41:42.150 --> 00:41:46.200 align:middle line:84%
Someone reminded me, there's no
tigers in the African savanna.

00:41:46.200 --> 00:41:49.290 align:middle line:84%
Fighting off lions
left and right.

00:41:49.290 --> 00:41:51.660 align:middle line:84%
Same stress,
different adaptations.

00:41:51.660 --> 00:41:54.310 align:middle line:90%


00:41:54.310 --> 00:41:59.870 align:middle line:84%
So the key is to
figure out what's

00:41:59.870 --> 00:42:04.850 align:middle line:84%
activating the fat programs in
you and turn those stresses off

00:42:04.850 --> 00:42:08.657 align:middle line:84%
and then to impose
other stresses that

00:42:08.657 --> 00:42:10.365 align:middle line:84%
will make your body
activate the get thin

00:42:10.365 --> 00:42:11.750 align:middle line:90%
or get eaten adaptation.

00:42:11.750 --> 00:42:14.453 align:middle line:90%


00:42:14.453 --> 00:42:17.120 align:middle line:84%
So in the Gabriel Method, I talk
about a number of stresses that

00:42:17.120 --> 00:42:18.370 align:middle line:90%
can activate the fat programs.

00:42:18.370 --> 00:42:22.160 align:middle line:84%
I'll just tell you
them quickly right now.

00:42:22.160 --> 00:42:25.970 align:middle line:90%
Number one is dieting.

00:42:25.970 --> 00:42:28.040 align:middle line:84%
Dieting activates the
fat programs, right?

00:42:28.040 --> 00:42:29.850 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:42:29.850 --> 00:42:30.650 align:middle line:90%
It's a famine.

00:42:30.650 --> 00:42:33.095 align:middle line:90%


00:42:33.095 --> 00:42:34.845 align:middle line:84%
That's the whole point
of the fat programs

00:42:34.845 --> 00:42:37.440 align:middle line:90%
is to protect you from famines.

00:42:37.440 --> 00:42:38.240 align:middle line:90%
So great.

00:42:38.240 --> 00:42:39.590 align:middle line:90%
It's brilliant logic.

00:42:39.590 --> 00:42:40.760 align:middle line:90%
It makes sense.

00:42:40.760 --> 00:42:42.110 align:middle line:90%
Calories in, calories out.

00:42:42.110 --> 00:42:43.280 align:middle line:90%
Cut your calories.

00:42:43.280 --> 00:42:44.360 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:42:44.360 --> 00:42:45.980 align:middle line:90%
Wrong.

00:42:45.980 --> 00:42:49.310 align:middle line:84%
Simply because it activates
your body's fat programs.

00:42:49.310 --> 00:42:53.318 align:middle line:84%
You lose weight, but your
body wants to be fatter.

00:42:53.318 --> 00:42:54.860 align:middle line:84%
So dieting forces
you to gain weight,

00:42:54.860 --> 00:42:57.650 align:middle line:84%
or dieting gets your body to
activate the fat programs.

00:42:57.650 --> 00:43:00.590 align:middle line:84%
But you can be eating
to your heart's content,

00:43:00.590 --> 00:43:03.950 align:middle line:84%
but you can still be in
a nutritional famine.

00:43:03.950 --> 00:43:07.662 align:middle line:90%


00:43:07.662 --> 00:43:09.370 align:middle line:84%
You can still be in
a nutritional famine.

00:43:09.370 --> 00:43:11.693 align:middle line:90%


00:43:11.693 --> 00:43:13.360 align:middle line:84%
And that's because
the food we eat today

00:43:13.360 --> 00:43:15.100 align:middle line:90%
is nutritionally barren.

00:43:15.100 --> 00:43:18.000 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't have the specific
nutrients we need in a way

00:43:18.000 --> 00:43:19.750 align:middle line:84%
that our bodies can
digest and assimilate.

00:43:19.750 --> 00:43:21.365 align:middle line:90%
It's invented food.

00:43:21.365 --> 00:43:22.990 align:middle line:84%
Now, I'm not telling
you to cut it out,

00:43:22.990 --> 00:43:24.790 align:middle line:84%
but I am telling
you to add foods

00:43:24.790 --> 00:43:26.560 align:middle line:84%
that have the nutrients
your body needs

00:43:26.560 --> 00:43:30.080 align:middle line:84%
in a way your body can
digest and assimilate

00:43:30.080 --> 00:43:32.600 align:middle line:84%
if your body's activating
the fat programs because

00:43:32.600 --> 00:43:33.890 align:middle line:90%
of a nutritional famine.

00:43:33.890 --> 00:43:36.388 align:middle line:84%
So what happens is, when
you're in a nutritional famine,

00:43:36.388 --> 00:43:38.180 align:middle line:84%
your body stays hungry
all the time looking

00:43:38.180 --> 00:43:39.790 align:middle line:90%
for these specific nutrients.

00:43:39.790 --> 00:43:42.000 align:middle line:84%
And you're not
giving it to them.

00:43:42.000 --> 00:43:44.450 align:middle line:84%
So it's not about
calories in, calories out.

00:43:44.450 --> 00:43:48.300 align:middle line:84%
And it's not about whether
it's carbs, proteins, or fats.

00:43:48.300 --> 00:43:49.450 align:middle line:90%
It's about what carbs?

00:43:49.450 --> 00:43:50.250 align:middle line:90%
What proteins?

00:43:50.250 --> 00:43:51.180 align:middle line:90%
What fats?

00:43:51.180 --> 00:43:53.960 align:middle line:84%
Have the specific
nutrients your body needs.

00:43:53.960 --> 00:43:56.920 align:middle line:90%


00:43:56.920 --> 00:44:00.220 align:middle line:84%
So I have two very
counter intuitive

00:44:00.220 --> 00:44:05.590 align:middle line:84%
counter to mainstream
wisdom messages

00:44:05.590 --> 00:44:06.940 align:middle line:90%
for the world about weight loss.

00:44:06.940 --> 00:44:12.070 align:middle line:84%
Number one is that obesity
is caused by starvation.

00:44:12.070 --> 00:44:15.290 align:middle line:84%
I bet no one's ever
told you that before.

00:44:15.290 --> 00:44:18.290 align:middle line:84%
Starvation, meaning
in some way, your body

00:44:18.290 --> 00:44:23.270 align:middle line:84%
